definitions.definition: Relating to a single person or thing as opposed to more than one.
examples: As we can't print them all together, the individual pages will have to be printed one by one.

definitions.definition: Intended for a single person as opposed to more than one person.
examples: individual personal pension; individual cream cakes

definitions.definition: Not divisible without losing its identity.
